# Build the data (for this example we'll create random points)
np.random.seed(42)
num_points = 80  

black_points = np.random.normal(loc=[1, 1], scale=0.2, size=(num_points, 2))
red_points = np.random.normal(loc=[1, 1], scale=0.8, size=(num_points * 2, 2))

##################
# Chart settings
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
plt.scatter(
    black_points[:, 0],  black_points[:, 1], 
    color='black', label='Black Points (1)', edgecolor='white', s=80)

plt.scatter(
    red_points[:, 0], red_points[:, 1], 
    color='red', label='Red Points (0)', edgecolor='black', s=80)

# Add tags and titles
plt.title("Decision Boundary and Filtered Points", fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
plt.xlabel("X-axis", fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel("Y-axis", fontsize=14)
plt.legend(fontsize=12)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
plt.xlim(-1, 3)
plt.ylim(-1, 3)

# Show chart
plt.show()

# Tags
X = np.vstack((black_points, red_points))
y = np.hstack((np.ones(len(black_points)), np.zeros(len(red_points))))

# Define the model with two layers and 4 neurons
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Input(shape=(2,)),  
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(4, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(4, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid') 
])
In [29]:
# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Distance function to detect points close to the border
def distance_from_center(points, center=[1, 1]):
    return np.linalg.norm(points - np.array(center), axis=1)

# Calculate the distance from the center
black_distances = distance_from_center(black_points)
red_distances = distance_from_center(red_points)

# Set the threshold for clearing points close to the border (for example: distance greater than 0.4)
threshold = 0.4
filtered_black_points = black_points[black_distances < threshold]
filtered_red_points = red_points[red_distances > threshold]

# Plot the data before and after cleaning
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

# Data before cleaning
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.scatter(black_points[:, 0], black_points[:, 1], color='black', label='Black Points')
plt.scatter(red_points[:, 0], red_points[:, 1], color='red', label='Red Points')
plt.title('Before Data Cleaning')
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Y')
plt.legend()

# Data after cleaning
plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.scatter(filtered_black_points[:, 0], filtered_black_points[:, 1], color='black', label='Filtered Black Points')
plt.scatter(filtered_red_points[:, 0], filtered_red_points[:, 1], color='red', label='Filtered Red Points')
plt.title('After Data Cleaning')
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Y')
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

preds = model.predict(grid).reshape(xx.shape)

# Chart settings
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))

    xx, yy, preds, levels=[0, 0.5, 1], alpha=0.3, colors=['#FF9999', '#999999', '#9999FF']
)

    filtered_black_points[:, 0], filtered_black_points[:, 1],

)
plt.scatter(

)

plt.ylabel("Y-axis", fontsize=14)

plt.ylim(-1, 3)

# Show chart
